The paper deals with semantic segmentation of medical images, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method uses meta-learning to improve the fusion module, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of weight sharing to reduce parameters, which is a technique used in both deep learning and neural networks (cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with medical images, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
